The '''olive-capped warbler''' ('''''Setophaga pityophila''''') is a species of [[New World warbler]] that is native to the [[Cuban pine forests#Western pine forests|western]] and [[Cuban pine forests#Eastern pine forests|eastern]] ends of [[Cuba]] as well as [[Grand Bahama]] and the [[Abaco Islands]] in [[Bahamian pineyards|the Bahamas]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is [[pine]] [[Tropical and subtropical coniferous forests|forests]] and occasionally adjacent mixed forests.

